# AI Image

## Summary
AiImage is the atomic "piece" of the package: one generated image modeled as its own card, so every version is independently referable, reusable, and carries a full generation record. It stores the `prompt` (String), the `mode` (an enum field: `'generate' | 'edit' | 'inpaint'`), the persisted result (`image = linksTo(ImageDef)`), an optional inpaint `mask = linksTo(ImageDef)` (white = repaint, black = keep), the `parent = linksTo(AiImage)` it was derived from (this self-referential edge forms the version tree), and the settings that produced it — `llmModel` (an enum of the OpenRouter image models), `aspectRatio` (AspectRatioField), and `createdAt` (DateTimeField). Because each generation is its own CardDef rather than a field on a bigger card, any image can be linked from anywhere and its lineage plus technique is always recoverable. The embedded format shows the image with a mode badge and prompt; the isolated format adds the full record (model, aspect ratio, inpaint mask, and the parent it was edited from).

## Import
```js
import { AiImage } from '../ai-image';
```

## Usage
AiImage is a card, so consuming cards link to it rather than containing it — the same wiring the generator uses for its ordered history:

```js
import { CardDef, field, linksToMany } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { AiImage } from '../ai-image';

export class Gallery extends CardDef {
  @field images = linksToMany(() => AiImage);
}
```
New AiImage records are produced by `GenerateAiImageCommand`, which fills in `image`, `mask`, `parent`, and the provenance fields in a single call — you rarely construct one by hand.

## Template Usage
```handlebars
<@fields.images @format='embedded' />
```
Renders each linked image with its mode badge and prompt; open one isolated to see its full generation record and parent lineage.
